signUp

TSignUpResult signUp(TAuthToken signupAuthToken,
                     java.lang.String accountMdn,
                     java.lang.String displayName,
                     java.lang.String email,
                     java.lang.String zipcode,
                     java.lang.String locale,
                     java.lang.String password,
                     boolean trialRequested,
                     java.util.List<TAssetInfo> assets,
                     boolean needToAddAllChildren,
                     TClientType clientType)
                     throws AuthenticationException.ServiceNotAvailable,
                            AuthorizationException.InvalidToken,
                            AuthorizationException.NotPermitted,
                            GatewayException,
                            OperationException.Duplicate,
                            OperationException.InvalidParameter,
                            OperationException.NoAssetsAdded,
                            OperationException.NotFound,
                            PersistException,
                            ServiceException
Creates a new account, without the REGISTRATION_INCOMPLETE flag but with the CHILD_CREATION_INCOMPLETE flag, and modifies the supplied auth token into a login token for that account.

Parameters:
signupAuthToken - auth token for this signup attempt
accountMdn - mdn to create account under
displayName - displayname to use
email - email address of record on account
zipcode - used to work out timezone
locale - language you want to use, null for default
password - new password
trialRequested - true if you would like a trial account
assets - assets to add
needToAddAllChildren - if true, then signup will fail if all supplied children could not be added. If false, signup will fail if none of the supplied children could be added.
clientType - the type of client which is being used to sign up.
Returns:
updated login info for the newly created account
Throws:
AuthenticationException.ServiceNotAvailable - if the requested service is not available for the mdn you specified
AuthorizationException.InvalidToken - if the supplied token is invalid
AuthorizationException.NotPermitted - if the token supplied is not allowed to create an account
GatewayException - if we can't communicate with an external service, eg carrier account service
OperationException.NotFound - if the specified mdn is not found on the account
OperationException.Duplicate - if the account that the caller requested to create already exists.
OperationException.InvalidParameter - if one of the supplied parameters has a bad value. Expected values are:
  • contactPhone
  • email
  • mdn
  • password
  • zipcode
PersistException - in the case of a db error
ServiceException - in the case of a serious error
OperationException.NoAssetsAdded - if the operation fails because no assets were added
